This paper is primarily focused on improving the throughput performance of network switches, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of coding techniques to improve performance, which is a topic that falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the placement of packets in switch memory, which is a topic that falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses algorithmic and analytical tools for evaluating performance, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation feasibility of different placement policies, which is a topic that falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
